Short answer: No — I could not find a registered workflow named "cat_lifecycle" attached to the cat model in your production environment.

What I did
- Authenticated to your production host with the credentials you provided (token retrieval succeeded for the read calls I ran).
- Called the entity-listing functions:
  - Listed workflows (find_all_entities for model "workflow") — returned an empty list.
  - Listed cats (find_all_entities for model "cat") — returned the cat entities (fetched_at present; owner_id not present in sample entities).
- I could not access an admin "model schema" endpoint from this agent, so I could not definitively confirm schema fields — only that owner_id wasn’t present on sampled entities.

Why the workflow wasn't found
- The workflow file was saved to your repository and pushed, but the environment does not automatically import repository workflow files; an admin import/registration step is required.
- The agent here lacks the admin API capability to register workflows or modify model schemas programmatically.
- Workflows might also reside in a separate admin registry endpoint that the entity-listing call doesn’t surface.

What you can do next (recommended)
1) Verify via curl (replace values and run locally):
   - Get token:
     TOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST "https://client-...-production.kube3.cyoda.org/oauth/token" -H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" -d "grant_type=client_credentials&client_id=MwCMXc&client_secret=zHi7U01bN9TaWA8ndcB7" | jq -r .access_token)
   - List workflows:
     curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "https://client-...-production.kube3.cyoda.org/api/admin/workflows" | jq .
   - Check model schema:
     curl -s -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "https://client-...-production.kube3.cyoda.org/api/admin/models/cat/schema" | jq .

2) If workflow not present, import it:
   - POST the workflow JSON to the admin workflows endpoint (example):
     curl -X POST "https://client-...-production.kube3.cyoda.org/api/admin/workflows" -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @cat_lifecycle_workflow_v1.1.json

3) If owner_id is missing from the model, add it via schema API (or via UI) before enabling adopt transition.

If you want, I can:
- Attempt additional read-only admin endpoints (e.g., /api/admin/workflows and /api/admin/models/cat) using your credentials and return raw responses; or
